<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Sealed Letter</title>

<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel&family=Uncial+Antiqua&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

<style>

body{
    margin:0;
    height:100vh;
    display:flex;
    justify-content:center;
    align-items:center;
    background:#1a1a1a;
    font-family:'Cinzel',serif;
}

/* wax seal screen */

#sealScreen{
    text-align:center;
    color:white;
}

.seal{
    width:120px;
    height:120px;
    background:#7a0f0f;
    border-radius:50%;
    display:flex;
    align-items:center;
    justify-content:center;
    font-size:40px;
    cursor:pointer;
    box-shadow:0 0 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
    margin:auto;
}

.seal:hover{
    transform:scale(1.05);
}

/* letter */

#letter{
    display:none;
    width:650px;
    max-width:90%;
    padding:60px;
    background:#f4ecd8;
    background-image:linear-gradient(#f4ecd8,#e6dcc4);
    border:8px solid #b89b6b;
    box-shadow:0 0 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.7);
    font-family:'Uncial Antiqua',serif;
    animation:fadeIn 2s;
}

@keyframes fadeIn{
    from{opacity:0; transform:translateY(30px);}
    to{opacity:1; transform:translateY(0);}
}

h1{
    text-align:center;
    margin-top:0;
}

</style>
</head>

<body>

<div id="sealScreen">
    <p>Click the seal to open the letter</p>
    <div class="seal" onclick="openLetter()">🜂</div>
</div>

<div id="letter">
<h1>A Sealed Message</h1>

<p>
My dearest Sir. Kameran Russell,
</p>

<p>
I hope this letter finds you in good health and in an unwearied enough state to read it.
</p>

<p>
Upon sitting myself down at my writing desk today to attend to my correspondence it came to me that I have not laid my eyes upon your visage in quite some time. Thus, I can only describe it as a weight off of my bosom to be penning this very letter to you now. In truth, I am not able to dedicate a nearly large enough time to the spending of it in your remarkable presence. As of this moment it is in great earnestness that I must inform you that I am quite taken with tasks about the ton. However, I have beheld with mine very own eyes that I have not yet acquired an engagement to dine tomorrow, not for a luncheon or even a bruncheon as it were. If none of this sound suitable I would like to invite you to take tea with me in the afternoon perhaps. It must not be a formal affair. I would be delighted to prepare a so-called ‘sandwich’ - I hear they are all the rage - for myself and accompany you as you descend upon the delicacy of bagels and creamed cheese that I hear you are most fond of. I may even be able to acquire such goods on my travels since I do plan on taking a promenade through the ton tomorrow. But I do not wish to smother you with such blatant interest in a meeting, it would be seen as improper for a young lady, and I do fear I have already overstepped. It is neither here nor there, but please do pen a response as soon as you are available.
</p>

<p>
In other news, I have been practically ravenous all day. It had been quite a strange feeling, and I do admit that it had overcome me quite suddenly. Such sporadic bursts of appetite are not uncommon I hear, but it does seem that I have been rather indulgent as of late. In such a manner as that I have been privy to some strong looks from the Lidl tradesmen as I stumbled out of their shop today with not one, not two, but three heads of broccoli. What I intend to do with them; I pray you do not ask of me. I fear I have fallen prey to what some call the ‘buy two get the third free’-trap. I mention this only because it seemed an odd and amusing thing that might enrich your day with some merriment. I do hope my jests and follies interest you. If you have any recommendations as to what to make of such an abundance of vegetable I pray you send word soon or I shall be forced to consume nothing but greens for the next fortnight.
</p>

<p>
I have many other things to tell you so it would be exquisite to be in your company soon as I am also most intrigued to discuss your new aspirations in the field of education. 
</p>

<p>
I hope your family is in good health and that the companions you lodge with are all of sound mind and body – a Sir. Olivier is of special interest in that regard as I have heard he has been prone to a sickly disposition as of late – and are in good spirits. 
</p>

<p>
I hope soon to be in your presence.
</p>

<p>
Yours sincerely and with love,
</p>

<p>
Written and sealed on the 27th of March 2026,
</p>

<p>
— Charlotte Senior
</p>

</div>

<script>

function openLetter(){
document.getElementById("sealScreen").style.display="none";
document.getElementById("letter").style.display="block";
}

</script>

</body>
</html>
